# ResolvedPDF: Comprehensive Ecosystem Report

This document provides a detailed technical overview of the **ResolvedPDF** project, its architecture, deployment environments, and a guide for future modifications.

## 1. Project Overview

ResolvedPDF is a multi-platform tool designed to convert custom [.resolved](file:///c:/Users/rehan/OneDrive/Desktop/Plugin/model_handoff.md.resolved) Markdown-style files into beautifully formatted PDF documents. The ecosystem consists of three primary interfaces:

1. **Local Desktop Application:** A Tkinter-based GUI for local conversion and premium key management.
2. **Web Application:** A FastAPI backend with a modern drag-and-drop frontend, deployed to Railway.
3. **Editor Extensions:** Integrations for Visual Studio Code (Microsoft Marketplace) and Antigravity/VSCodium (Open VSX Registry).

---

## 2. System Architecture & Flow

The ecosystem relies on a shared core conversion logic, adapted for each platform.

### High-Level Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph "User Interfaces"
        VSCode["VS Code / Antigravity Extension\n(TypeScript)"]
        WebAppUI["Web App Frontend\n(HTML/JS, Drag & Drop)"]
        DesktopApp["Desktop GUI\n(Python/Tkinter)"]
    end

    subgraph "Core Logic (Python)"
        Converter["convert_resolved.py\n(ReportLab engine)"]
        Usage["usage_tracker.py\n(Rate limiting & Premium logic)"]
    end

    subgraph "Web Backend (FastAPI)"
        MainPY["main.py"]
        Server["Uvicorn / Railway"]
    end

    VSCode -->|Spawns external process| Converter
    DesktopApp --> Converter
    DesktopApp --> Usage
    
    WebAppUI -->|POST /convert| MainPY
    MainPY --> Converter
    MainPY --> Usage
    MainPY -->|Returns Blob| WebAppUI
```

---

## 3. Component Details & Internal Working

### 3.1 Core Converter ([convert_resolved.py](file:///c:/Users/rehan/OneDrive/Desktop/Plugin/convert_resolved.py))
This is the heart of the application. It parses the custom markdown format and renders it into a PDF.

*   **Engine:** Uses `reportlab.platypus` (PageTemplates, Paragraphs, Tables) to construct the document flow.
*   **Parsing Logic:** It reads the text line by line, identifying:
    *   `# Heading 1`, `## Heading 2`, `### Heading 3`
    *   ```code blocks```
    *   `| Table | Rows |`
    *   `**Bold**` and `*Italic*` text.
*   **Styling:** Contains a predefined [build_styles()](file:///c:/Users/rehan/OneDrive/Desktop/Plugin/convert_resolved.py#41-90) function that sets fonts (Helvetica), colors (professional light theme), and spacing.
*   **Process:**
    1.  Reads the input string.
    2.  Tokenizes/parses the markdown into ReportLab *Flowables* (Paragraph, Table, Preformatted).
    3.  Builds the PDF document using `SimpleDocTemplate`.

### 3.2 Web Application (`webapp/`)
A fully containerized web service designed for public access.

*   **Backend ([main.py](file:///c:/Users/rehan/OneDrive/Desktop/Plugin/webapp/main.py)):** Uses FastAPI. Exposes the HTML frontend and an API endpoint (`/convert`).
*   **Rate Limiting ([usage_tracker.py](file:///c:/Users/rehan/OneDrive/Desktop/Plugin/usage_tracker.py)):** Implements IP-based rate limiting (default 3/day) tracked via a local JSON file (`.usage_data.json`). Premium keys bypass this limit.
*   **Frontend ([templates/index.html](file:///c:/Users/rehan/OneDrive/Desktop/Plugin/webapp/templates/index.html)):** A modern, responsive single-page application using vanilla JS. Handles drag-and-drop, API communication, and automatic file downloading upon success.
*   **Deployment (Railway):**
    *   Uses Nixpacks for automated building.
    *   [Procfile](file:///c:/Users/rehan/OneDrive/Desktop/Plugin/Procfile) and [nixpacks.toml](file:///c:/Users/rehan/OneDrive/Desktop/Plugin/nixpacks.toml) ensure correct dependency installation from [requirements.txt](file:///c:/Users/rehan/OneDrive/Desktop/Plugin/requirements.txt) and correct start commands (`cd webapp && python -m uvicorn...`).

### 3.3 Editor Extensions (`vscode-extension/`)
Provides seamless integration directly within code editors.

*   **Language:** TypeScript/Node.js.
*   **Functionality:** Registers a command (`resolvedpdf.convert`) that appears in the editor and file explorer context menus for files ending in [.resolved](file:///c:/Users/rehan/OneDrive/Desktop/Plugin/model_handoff.md.resolved).
*   **Execution:** When triggered, the extension uses `child_process.spawn` to execute a bundled version of [convert_resolved.py](file:///c:/Users/rehan/OneDrive/Desktop/Plugin/convert_resolved.py) against the selected file.
*   **Publishing Platforms:**
    *   **Microsoft Marketplace:** Target: Standard VS Code. Publisher: `vibecoder`. Tool: `vsce publish`.
    *   **Open VSX Registry:** Target: Antigravity, VSCodium, Gitpod. Publisher: `vibecoder111`. Tool: `ovsx publish`.

### Extension Execution Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Editor as VS Code / Antigravity
    participant Extension as extension.ts
    participant Python as convert_resolved.py
    participant FileSystem

    User->>Editor: Right-clicks file.resolved
    User->>Editor: Selects "Convert to PDF"
    Editor->>Extension: Triggers resolvedpdf.convert(URI)
    Extension->>Extension: Validates file extension & existence
    Extension->>Python: child_process.spawn('python', [scriptPath, input, output])
    Extension->>User: Shows "Converting..." progress
    Python->>FileSystem: Reads file.resolved
    Python->>FileSystem: Writes file.pdf
    Python-->>Extension: Process Exits (Code 0)
    Extension->>User: Shows Success Notification
    User->>Extension: Clicks "Open PDF"
    Extension->>Editor: Opens PDF in default viewer
```

